com.google.gwt.user.client.EventListener, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.HasFocus, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.HasWidgets, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesFocusEvents, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesKeyboardEvents, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesTableEvents, com.google.gwt.widgetideas.table.client.SourceTableSelectionEvents, java.lang.Iterable<com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget>, HasFastTreeTableItems
public class FastTreeTable
extends com.google.gwt.widgetideas.table.client.FixedWidthGrid
implements com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.HasFocus, HasFastTreeTableItems

A standard hierarchical tree widget. The tree contains a hierarchy of FastTreeItems.

CSS Style Rules

  • .gwt-FastTree { the tree itself }
  • .gwt-FastTree .gwt-FastTreeItem { a tree item }
  • .gwt-FastTree .selection-bar {the selection bar used to highlight the selected tree item}

Author:
georgopoulos.georgios(at)gmail.com

processElementClicked

protected boolean processElementClicked(FastTreeTableItem item)
This is called when a valid selectable element is clicked in the tree. Subclasses can override this method to decide whether or not FastTree should keep processing the element clicked. For example, a subclass may decide to return false for this method if selecting a new item in the tree is subject to asynchronous approval from other components of the application.
